{"name":"Trade","permission":{"default":0,"rbcGjlrp2ErJQnBu":3},"type":"skill","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Trade (Smarts) </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">is for day-to-day tasks needed to run a business (blacksmith, saloon owner, miner, etc.). Note the specific trade in parentheses. Trade lets an entrepreneur raise funds (as the Performance skill in </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\">Savage Worlds</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">) through advertising, money-saving tactics, and buying cheaper goods.</span></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Raising Funds: </span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The amount of money a character can raise by trade skill is extremely subjective, but as a general rule a successful trade raises 20% of the setting’s Starting Funds with a success and 30% with a raise. The GM can multiply this amount by the trader's Rank if she feels it’s</span>&nbsp; <span class=\"fontstyle0\">appropriate. These numbers work for typical traders who might be known in a small establishment or area. Larger performances can greatly boost the trader’s fee, but also require more time, energy, and setup.</span></p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","die":{"sides":4,"modifier":"0"},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skill.svg","_id":"XHADG1Xca7cx5zPe"}
